author: China Insights-SOHTV
description: On June 3, 2025, a young man charged toward the flagpole in Tiananmen Square, only to be tackled by police and vanish without a trace. This chilling scene echoes the brutal crackdown of the 1984 "64" student protests, where calls for democracy were silenced by tanks and bullets. Thirty-five years later, the CCP’s grip remains tight—censoring, suppressing, and erasing dissent. Yet, one question lingers: have the people forgotten? This bold act of defiance proves resistance is still alive. Dare to watch and uncover the truth. #Tiananmen #HumanRights #China
title: Tiananmen 2025: Young Man Tackled, Vanished—Is Resistance Still Alive?#shorts

description:
Jiang Yurong, a Harvard Kennedy School graduate, gave an emotional speech on “shared humanity,” but her deep ties to the Chinese Communist Party, possible military connections, and involvement in the 2024 Xie Feng speech protest crackdown tell a different story.

She directed the removal of Tibetan and Taiwanese protesters at Harvard during Chinese Ambassador Xie Feng’s speech, raising serious questions about her true allegiance.

Explore how the CCP uses elite U.S. universities like Harvard to groom officials, spread propaganda, and possibly link to military interests worldwide.

🔔 Subscribe for more on China, CCP influence, and global politics.
